column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Heavy recreational use on 7/4- 50% cloud cover- mid 80'sf
Has been cool- wind at 5 mph- approximately 50% cloud cover
Clear- low 80'sf- light to medium use lately
Very warm for several days (90's) - traffic on lake has dropped significantly
Once again low boat traffic.  Seems to be the boats that cause the water clarity problem.
Very windy with bottom turn up.  It was hard to do the test- too windy.
No boat action- bottom not turned up- carp are moving around.
Overcast- weed harvesting the previous day
We found a deeper part of the lake
Used test disk 6.5'- and regular disk 6.25'
Very windy can not hold in the deep hole area
New disk works great in the wind because it drops so quickly
Very low boat traffic- could see a dime on the bottom.
Ice off 4-4-94.  Let the fun begin!
Swimming + aesthetic enjoyment slightly impaired because of bottom sediment.  Bad weather- lots of wind throughout week.
Sediment in lake- lots of waves
There was a lot of boat action throughout the week.
Very poor water clarity- a lot of boat action.
Water level still low - better is starting to rise.
This summer seems to be poor water clarity of our lake.
Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 1'.
Very low boat traffic throughout the week.
Moderate boat traffic throughout the week.
Very low boat traffic throughout the week.
First  measurement; training with Laura Herman.
Overcast- breezy- difficult to see disc although water seemed clear.
Overcast and breezy. Lake still somewhat stirred up from weekend boat traffic.
Partly cloudy- somewhat overcast. Light breeze- water was calm.
Bright- calm day; helped by granddaughters- Grace + Lilly.
Clear- sunny- light winds. Helped by wife- Julie.
Beautiful- sunny day. Breeze out of the east. Lake seemed "stirred up"- although it had not been busy with boats or windy for the last several days.
With Julie; sunny- mild. light breeze out of SE.
Overcast- breeze out of Southwest.  Granddaughter- Lilly Cobb helped.
Beautiful day low 70s; helped by Julie. Eelgrass is quite thick and going to seed.
w/Julie. Lots of EWM and suspended particles but  water is fairly clear. Sunny- light breeze- upper 70s.
Helped by granddaughters Grace and Lilly. Weather unsettled and overcast - over an inch of rain last night.
Partly cloudy- breezy- low 70s. Wife Julie helped. Lots of milfoil this year. Secchi got buried in the plants. Appearance of algae in water column close to shore where it is calm.
Sunny- fairly calm- with wife- Julie. We now appear to have a resident seagull! The eel grass is flourishing. The secchi disc gets lost in the plants and hard to read as a result.
Calm- sunny day - low 70s. EWM not up in most areas yet- except Pickerel Bay. With Tom Day. Plenty of carp. Algae was evident.
Overcast- 70- light breeze. difficult to tell water color. Helped by wife- Julie. EWM seems less aggressive this year.

Weather is clear in low 70s with north breeze. Wife- Julie helped. Secchi got wrapped in eelgrass before it hit bottom so reading depth understates the clarity. Weather is clear in low 70s with north breeze. Wife- Julie helped. Secchi got wrapped in eelgrass before it hit bottom so reading depth understates the clarity.
Clear- sunny- mild. Eelgrass is going to seed and very thick- hopefully crowding out the EWM. By hunting for an open spot (few tall plants) I was able to see the secchi all the way to the bottom.
Mid 60s- sunny- beautiful day.Eel grass is uprooting. Secchi depth reading limited by depth and plants. Clarity is excellent.
Sunny- with Tom Day- saw a couple of heron.
Very calm and sunny. Helped by granddaughters.
Partly cloudy- mild. With Julie Mann
Cloudy- overcast- cool. With Julie Mann. Lots of eel grace going to seed.
Beautiful day - sunny- breezy- low 70s. Wife Julie helped.
Beautiful day - sunny- 75- little wind. With Julie Mann. Greenish/yellow algae is quite visible.
84 degrees- clear skies- breeze out of NNW. With Julie Mann. Algae is quite prevalent along shore and in water column.
Beautiful day - clear sky- mid 70s- wind NW. With Wife- Julie.
Cloudy- rain in forecast.  Cloudy- rain in forecast.  Recent heavy (over 3") rain night before last.
Beautiful day- with wife Julie. Breeze out of Northeast.
Beautiful fall day. Lake is quite clear. Helped by Greg H. Beautiful fall day. Lake is quite clear. Helped by Greg H. This is my August sample and it will be refrigerated until Tuesday.
Partly cloudy- breeze out of the North; light chop- 70 degrees. With Julie.
Cool- sunny- light wind from north; with Julie.
Cloudy- overcast- very little wind. With Tom Day.
Partly cloudy- breezy- out of the north. Very nice day.
Mostly sunny- breezy; w/Julie. We had 1 3/4" of rain within last 24 hours.
Sunny- hot- and breezy. Light boat traffic but no more than a normal week day.
Sunny- hot- and breezy. With Julie.
